"What is this... I wonder..."\n<Yukine>\F[5]

A month-long drought withered many crops, and
starving people began to die one after another,
wandering in search of food.

Some spread rumors of hidden rice, and we took up
our farm tools in anger. Men begged for mercy,
lying prostrate, but were met with the swing of a
hoe, ending their lives.

Though the bales were empty, the starving
relentlessly tilled their backs. The beastly acts
committed by those we once called friends were
unbearable to witness.

Women disturbed, running to their children, seeing
the shadows of their deceased offspring in the
emaciated living ones, but unable to reach them.
Only the dead increased in their desolate homes.

Without a glance from those who could help, all
was abandoned. We are no longer human; unworthy of
salvation from gods or Buddha.

girl wandering alone from village to village with
a sinister smile.

Those who approached the girl all went mad; some
bit the earth and choked, others devoured dry
grass and died, and some gnawed on farm tools in
their insanity.

Could this be divine punishment? I am simply
terrified, so terrified.
